Mzansi women are fast making names for themselves in the world
of car spinning. WOMEN from different spinning clubs in Mzansi came to Wheelz
n Smoke in the south of Joburg to celebrate National Women's Day. It was called Spinderella with the theme 'Power under her
Foot'. It was created to
open doors for women in spinning and drifting and also to put a stop to it as a
male dominated sport. Women participants included fearless teenager, Kaylin
Oliphant (17) from Kimberley in the Northern Cape. An overall winner
received a floating trophy. PHOTOS BY PICTURE HELLO  